If you&#39;d like to visualize API&#39;s using `Swagger`, I&#39;d suggest to follow this simple tutorial.

No additional configurations required !

**Simple steps** 

1) Add below dependency 

&lt;dependency&gt;

    &lt;groupId&gt;org.springdoc&lt;/groupId&gt;

    &lt;artifactId&gt;springdoc-openapi-ui&lt;/artifactId&gt;

    &lt;version&gt;1.6.4&lt;/version&gt;

&lt;/dependency&gt;


2) Access API after starting your Spring boot app at following path in browser

`http://localhost:your_port/v3/api-docs/`

3) Use a custom path by modifying property , for e.g.

`springdoc.api-docs.path=/api-docs`

4) Default integration is also available with below link

`http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html`

**Follow this short and sweet tutorial** https://www.baeldung.com/spring-rest-openapi-documentation

